info.senderName: NWS Cheyenne (Southeastern Wyoming and Western Nebraska)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 24 at 10:55AM MST until December 25 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM 5 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 11 PM MST SUNDAY... ...HIGH WIND WARNING WILL EXPIRE AT 11 AM MST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Sustained west winds 30 to 40 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH. * WHERE...South Laramie Range. * WHEN...From 5 PM this afternoon to 11 PM MST Sunday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
